name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: No matter what's happening in life, big or small, it's ok not to be OK. There's help. name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: Wells Fargo will pay over a half-billion dollars to resolve states’ allegations of rampant #ConsumerProtection violations in its sales, mortgage, and auto-lending practices. NJ will receive nearly $17M. Read More:  https://t.co/HKmA4nyoJd

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: NJ’s legislature has restricted predatory, high-interest payday lending in our state. We are taking action with @AGKarlRacine and other AGs to prevent out-of-state companies from skirting the state laws that protect our residents from these predatory practices.  https://t.co/60ZAHCrKGq

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: NJ Bureau of Securities ordered Complete Business Solutions Group d/b/a PAR Funding to stop selling unregistered securities related to cash-advance industry. We're working hard to protect investors & consumers from those who violate NJ's securities laws:  https://t.co/fqfY7sH7O8

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: Warm thoughts to those marking the beginning of Kwanzaa tonight with the lighting of the kinara and celebration of the seven principles --unity, self-determination, collective work, cooperative economics, purpose, creativity, and faith.

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: Over the past year, we've worked hard to protect New Jersey residents from the worst of the Trump Administration's environmental rollbacks. There's much more to do, and we won't give up the fight for clean air, clean water, and environmental justice for all.   Onward to 2019.

tweet: Merry Christmas from @NewJerseyOAG! #MerryChristmas #ChristmasMorning

tweet: Grateful to have the support of @GovMurphy, @SenatorMenendez, @SenBooker, @FrankPallone, and so many others as we fight the federal government's plans to drill for oil off New Jersey's coast.    Together, we'll protect our coastline for future generations.  https://t.co/4JqdWAOTK2

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: In October, we joined 18 AGs in opposing new DOJ rules that make it harder for people fleeing domestic abuse and gang violence to get asylum. Today, a federal judge agreed: the new rules violate the country's immigration laws. We're proud to put a stop to those misguided rules.  https://t.co/3O0U3O23cN

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: Congratulations to the JJC and the AOC for receiving an award from the @AECFNews in recognition of NJ's implementation of statewide juvenile detention reform.  NJ has been a JDAI model site for 10 years. Since implementing JDAI, NJ reduced its juvenile detention population by 70%  https://t.co/4It8qao4h3
